.TH KPM 1 "January 2026" "0.0.1" "KSharp Package Manager Manual"
.SH NAME
kpm \- Professional-grade decentralized package manager for KSharp
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B kpm
[\fIcommand\fR] [\fIarguments\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B kpm
is a decentralized package manager for the KSharp (K#) ecosystem. It treats URLs as package identities and uses Git to fetch source code directly from remote repositories into a local cache.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B init <name>
Initialize a new KSharp project structure (src/, test/, and kmod.k).
.TP
.B get <url> [version]
Fetch a package and its dependencies. Aliases: \fBinstall\fR.
.TP
.B list
List all globally installed packages in the cache. Aliases: \fBls\fR.
.TP
.B remove <url>
Remove a package from the global cache. Aliases: \fBrm\fR, \fBuninstall\fR.
.TP
.B tidy
Resolve and install missing dependencies for the current project based on kmod.k. Aliases: \fBresolve\fR.
.TP
.B help
Display usage information and command reference.
.SH FILES
.I ~/.ksharp/modules/
Global cache directory where modules are stored in a domain-based hierarchy.
